{
  "stem": "15721.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they really thought that if they were much like the Nazis or thought much like the Nazis about many issues that they would thereby gain for themselves protection and acceptance because they kidded themselves because the Nazis were really not interested in ideology or in ideas.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were interested in the racial, biological component, as they called it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so they did escape as little as anybody else.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I remember since I lived in Munich there was the brown house, as it was called, the headquarters of the Nazi Party.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And Hitler and his inner circle not only lived there, but they were often on the street.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Across the street from us was a house in which a man by the name of Ritter von Epp lived, who later became the-- the governor of Bavaria when Hitler came to power.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And Hitler and Goering and Goebbels in their open Mercedes limousines would drive up and visit there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I could lean out of the window and just, you know, look down across the street and see these open big touring cars and this whole gang assembling there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then I had a-- a personal experience-- actually, two.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "On the day that Hitler had become the chancellor of Germany, which was January 30th 1933, a date I won't ever forget, I was coming-- well, it must have been actually the next day because that was the evening.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I was coming from Hebrew school, which was downtown because there were so few Jews in any of the high schools that we were collected centrally and given instruction by a teacher there while, of course, in Bavaria at the time, the Lutherans and the Catholics got their religious instruction right in the high school.",
      "word_count": 55
    }
  ],
